00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:16,200
Xu Fang, you were great today.

257
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:19,200
Who are you?

258
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:21,100
I'm Lin Xichi's roommate.

259
00:24:21,100 --> 00:24:23,200
We're in the same English class.

260
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,600
My name is Xin Zidan.

261
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:27,400
Thank you all for coming.

262
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:30,200
Don't mention it!

263
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:40,000
You're such a big eater.

264
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,000
Stop stealing my meat!

265
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,000
There are so many, why did you steal mine?

266
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,900
Eat more vegetables! It's good for you.

267
00:24:47,600 --> 00:24:49,500
Here, eat more!

268
00:24:52,800 --> 00:24:55,000
People who don't know might think our team has been mistreating you.

269
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:56,800
Are you that hungry?

270
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:07,100
Don't you love eating this?

271
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:08,700
Eat more!

272
00:25:09,800 --> 00:25:11,800
But the meat is all gone.

273
00:25:11,800 --> 00:25:14,000
All that's left is chili.

274
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:23,300
Lin Xichi, you have no idea how Xu Fang bullies me.

275
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:27,900
He always bullies me.

276
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:31,700
- Let's go.
- Why did he drink so much?

277
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,400
I'm full, too! I'll go get the bill.

278
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,800
- Go on!
- It's on the team! Finish everything.

279
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:42,500
Sure.

280
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:51,600
There are so many dishes, why are you fighting over this with me?

281
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:55,000
I'm sorry, people call me Prawn Hunter.

282
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
And prawn is my favorite.

283
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,700
Sorry, my nickname is Prawn Huntsman.

284
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,400
This is mine!

285
00:26:01,400 --> 00:26:03,400
Give me a reason first.

286
00:26:03,400 --> 00:26:05,400
I made those posters.

287
00:26:05,400 --> 00:26:07,500
You made them?

288
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,400
I'm sorry! I didn't know that.

289
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,000
It's okay.

290
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:17,300
So, you're the one who made them.

291
00:26:17,300 --> 00:26:22,000
I was wondering who made such beautiful posters.

292
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:23,800
I never thought I'd see the maker today.

293
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:26,100
- What's your name?
- I'm Nie Yue.

294
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:27,700
What a good name.

295
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:30,000
- I'm...
- Jiang Zheng Xu. Your father is a Chinese medicine practitioner.

296
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,400
- I remember you.
- Do you?

297
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:35,800
Well, when I made your poster, your face was my source of inspiration, you know?

298
00:26:35,800 --> 00:26:38,300
Because you look like

299
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:41,000
a Chinese medicine practitioner.

300
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:46,400
You have a sense of humor.

301
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,700
Nie Yue, I have a request.

302
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:51,500
I'd like to keep those posters.

303
00:26:51,500 --> 00:26:54,100
But Lin Xichi wanted me to pay for them.

304
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:57,000
I still have them! I have many copies in my room, I printed more than we needed.

305
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,400
- You have them?
- I'll give them to you later.

306
00:26:58,400 --> 00:27:00,200
Sure, just give me all of them.

307
00:27:00,200 --> 00:27:02,800
I'm going to paste them on my wall.

308
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,300
So cool.

309
00:27:08,159 --> 00:27:09,698
Let's have five more plates.

310
00:27:09,698 --> 00:27:11,400
Lin Xichi went to pay for the bill.

311
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:14,600
Why did she do so? I said that I'd pay for it.

312
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:16,600
You should go before she does, she's just went to the counter.

313
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:18,400
Sure, I'll go find her now.

314
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:21,800
- I'll have five more plates of prawns without corns.
- No, one plate is enough.

315
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:24,300
No, five plates! Bye.

316
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,300
Wait for me!

317
00:27:29,300 --> 00:27:30,700
Slowly.

318
00:27:30,700 --> 00:27:33,300
I'm not done drinking.

319
00:27:34,800 --> 00:27:37,100
- Keep drinking.
- Taxi!

320
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,600
We'll leave first!

321
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:41,400
Let's go!

322
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:47,500
- We're off!
- Bye-bye.

323
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,400
Xu Fang,

324
00:28:01,900 --> 00:28:04,100
do you like Lin Xichi?

325
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:10,300
I take your silence as denial.

326
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,800
What does that have to do with you?

327
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:16,800
It does.

328
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:20,600
Because liking someone doesn't depend on who met them first.

329
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:26,000
Try it then!

330
00:28:44,000 --> 00:28:47,600
Lin Xichi, it's late, where have you been?

331
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:51,300
Where have you been? You disappeared from the meal.

332
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:56,300
Fang-fang, you smell like alcohol.

333
00:28:56,300 --> 00:28:58,200
Did you drink?

334
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:03,000
It seems that the archery team has had fun tonight.

335
00:29:08,200 --> 00:29:09,900
Chi-chi,

336
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:13,400
I want to apologize to you.

337
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:16,900
Sure, you owe me one hundred thousand apologies.

338
00:29:16,900 --> 00:29:20,000
Which one are you going to say first?

339
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,900
When we were in high school.

340
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:25,200
That's a long time ago.

341
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:29,600
It's the night we were looking for Fang Fang.

342
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:36,400
It was a rainy night and I said many horrible things.

343
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:39,600
Looking back,

344
00:29:40,300 --> 00:29:43,800
I realize that I didn't stand in your shoes.

345
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:46,900
I was trying to comfort you using my own way,

346
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:49,600
but that method didn't suit you.

347
00:29:49,600 --> 00:29:51,800
and hurt you instead.

348
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:55,700
It's all in the past, why do you bring it up now?

349
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:57,300
Chi-chi,

350
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,900
I'm sorry.

351
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,900
Actually, I've long forgiven you.

352
00:30:07,900 --> 00:30:10,800
Did you know I went to find you the next day?

353
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:13,300
But you weren't home.

354
00:30:13,300 --> 00:30:15,200
I went to find you, too!

355
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:18,600
But you moved to your grandfather's and I was downstairs at his place...

356
00:30:20,600 --> 00:30:23,200
but I felt ashamed to call you.

357
00:30:25,600 --> 00:30:27,800
Then, we're even now.

358
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,000
Chi-chi,

359
00:30:35,940 --> 00:30:37,540
I...

360
00:30:38,580 --> 00:30:43,080
I... I... I like-I like...

361
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:46,439
The bike is new, you don't need to wash it.
(TN: "like" and "wash" have the same homonym.)

362
00:30:47,419 --> 00:30:49,459
Let me ride it!

363
00:30:49,459 --> 00:30:51,560
Let me ride it.

364
00:30:52,419 --> 00:30:54,258
Let me ride it.

365
00:30:54,258 --> 00:30:56,399
What? Forget about it!

366
00:30:56,399 --> 00:30:59,120
You've always been petty when it comes to bikes.

367
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:01,539
You said you wanted to apologize to me.

368
00:31:01,539 --> 00:31:03,499
Let me ride it

369
00:31:03,499 --> 00:31:05,298
and I'll forgive you.

370
00:31:05,298 --> 00:31:06,799
I don't need your forgiveness.

371
00:31:06,799 --> 00:31:09,998
But you were asking for it! Give me the key.

372
00:31:09,998 --> 00:31:11,680
- No.
- I was the one who chose the prize.

373
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:13,200
Come and get it.

374
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:22,200
Do you like it?

375
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:24,679
I'll gift it to you.

376
00:31:25,559 --> 00:31:28,049
- Really?
- If you don't want, then just forget about it.

377
00:31:28,049 --> 00:31:31,259
- Don't want?!
♫ but you are already laughing at something, ♫

378
00:31:31,260 --> 00:31:34,468
♫ whether you understand or not, ♫

379
00:31:35,083 --> 00:31:37,840
♫ or pretend to be indifferent. ♫

380
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:38,986
Come, let's go for a ride!

381
00:31:38,986 --> 00:31:41,471
♫ If only I could remove your sadness. ♫

382
00:31:42,047 --> 00:31:45,656
♫ Afraid some words would breakdown the mask, ♫

383
00:31:45,656 --> 00:31:47,760
♫ suddenly, I found myself speechless. ♫

384
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:49,578
What an awesome bike!

385
00:31:49,578 --> 00:31:51,999
- One can even change the speed!
- Be careful!

386
00:31:51,999 --> 00:31:56,750
♫ You are chatting about the plot of a dream ♫

387
00:31:57,586 --> 00:32:04,169
♫ and sadly, cry your eyes out. ♫

388
00:32:05,040 --> 00:32:06,916
I feel as if I'm going to fly!

389
00:32:06,917 --> 00:32:10,625
♫ Love is like a migratory bird waiting for the season. ♫

390
00:32:12,326 --> 00:32:15,178
Chi-chi,
♫ How long does it take for them to be aware of each other? ♫

391
00:32:15,179 --> 00:32:17,179
thank you.

392
00:32:17,179 --> 00:32:20,762
♫ You are like summer night, ♫

393
00:32:20,762 --> 00:32:24,440
♫ I'm like a little star in the sky, ♫

394
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:29,379
♫ accompanying you to blink until indispensable. ♫

395
00:32:29,379 --> 00:32:33,579
Lin Xichi, are you okay? Get up, get up!

396
00:32:33,579 --> 00:32:35,378
- Is your bike okay?
- Are you hurt? Let me check!

397
00:32:35,378 --> 00:32:38,459
Who cares about the bike. Get up first!

398
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:42,619
I'm fine.

399
00:32:42,619 --> 00:32:44,780
I'll send you back.

400
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:48,699
- What about this?
- I don't want this shabby bike.

401
00:32:48,699 --> 00:32:52,300
No, you can't throw away your prize. I like it!

402
00:32:53,379 --> 00:32:55,410
Carry it.

403
00:32:56,279 --> 00:32:57,920
Why are you looking at me?

404
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,980
I carry it?

405
00:33:01,866 --> 00:33:03,666
I'll carry it.

406
00:33:05,019 --> 00:33:07,119
Hurry up!

407
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:10,159
Although I'm limping, I can walk faster than you.

408
00:33:10,159 --> 00:33:12,440
- You...
- Can you carry it?

409
00:33:12,440 --> 00:33:14,500
You should try to carry it.

410
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:18,060
It's so tiring, I'm exhausted!

411
00:33:18,060 --> 00:33:19,620
I can't walk anymore.

412
00:33:19,620 --> 00:33:21,740
Are you crazy?

413
00:33:23,540 --> 00:33:27,380
♪ We met in our youth. ♪

414
00:33:27,380 --> 00:33:31,400
♪ We wrote down the pure vow. ♪

415
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:34,760
♪ Before the summer came, ♪

416
00:33:36,580 --> 00:33:38,400
♪ we met. ♪

417
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:41,580
Are you still letting people sleep?

418
00:33:41,580 --> 00:33:43,340
Lower your voice!

419
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:05,300
So, how did it go?

420
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:06,539
How did it go?

421
00:34:06,539 --> 00:34:09,440
Did you confess to her in the middle of the night?

422
00:34:16,080 --> 00:34:17,880
What?

423
00:34:19,380 --> 00:34:21,560
She didn't accept you?

424
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,639
It's okay.

425
00:34:24,639 --> 00:34:26,740
She doesn't like you.

426
00:34:26,740 --> 00:34:30,760
That's her loss, isn't it?

427
00:34:30,760 --> 00:34:34,160
Where could she find a good childhood friend like you?

428
00:34:35,260 --> 00:34:38,580
When I see her one of these days,

429
00:34:38,580 --> 00:34:40,380
I'll scold her.

430
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:44,120
Don't get upset!

431
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:45,860
Yeah.

432
00:34:45,860 --> 00:34:49,040
Since you've confessed to her,

433
00:34:50,100 --> 00:34:52,760
you'll feel awkward meeting her.

434
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:55,000
You might even lose her as a friend.

435
00:34:56,620 --> 00:34:58,380
I didn't confess to her.

436
00:35:01,400 --> 00:35:03,200
What?

437
00:35:04,320 --> 00:35:06,620
You didn't do it?

438
00:35:06,620 --> 00:35:08,440
Then, what did you do?

439
00:35:08,440 --> 00:35:10,920
You went for a walk? You–

440
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:14,119
It was a good opportunity, why didn't you confess to her?

441
00:35:14,119 --> 00:35:16,760
I didn't know how to do it.

442
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:19,059
What are you talking about?

443
00:35:19,059 --> 00:35:21,630
It's not hard at all.

444
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:25,200
Just be casual, close your eyes, and tell her you like her.

445
00:35:25,200 --> 00:35:27,080
Isn't that easy?

446
00:35:28,420 --> 00:35:30,520
What's so hard about it?

447
00:35:34,060 --> 00:35:39,160
Look! I saw it extremely clearly during the meal.

448
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:42,160
Ye Shaowen has intentions towards Lin Xichi.

449
00:35:43,940 --> 00:35:45,979
You're able to deal with one Fu Kuankuan.

450
00:35:45,979 --> 00:35:49,220
But you can't deal with another one.

451
00:35:49,220 --> 00:35:51,920
That guy is evil.

452
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:55,080
You understand?

453
00:35:56,780 --> 00:36:00,300
Having a crush on someone sounds like a beautiful thing.

454
00:36:00,300 --> 00:36:02,740
Actually, it's like eating wax.

455
00:36:02,740 --> 00:36:06,480
Listen! If someone gets her before you do,

456
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:08,760
